<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05039g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05039g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05039g"> 39(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> prefer altar to pulpit</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Fr. Burke told Bishop Delany that for effective preaching he <mark>preferred the altar to the pulpit</mark>. In the latter he was &lsquo;cabined and confined;&rsquo; the advantages afforded by the broader stage are obvious. <small> William J. Fitz-Patrick, <a name="BURKE" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BURKE"><cite title="source">The Life of the Very Rev. Thomas N. Burke</cite></a>, (1885) II, 153 [Retreat at Maynooth]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
